[00:00.00]As he held on he became more and more conscious of the new stir in the land. There was life abroad in it different from the life which had been there throughout the summer.  No longer was this fact borne in upon him in some subtle, mysterious way. The birds talked of it, the squirrels chattered about it, the very breeze whispered of it. 
