[01:04.98]His nose gave him a varying description of the passage of the life on the heels of which he was travelling.  He remarked the pregnant silence of the forest. The bird life had flitted. The squirrels were in hiding.  One only he saw,-a sleek gray fellow, flattened against a gray dead limb so that he seemed a part of it, a woody excrescence upon the wood itself. 
